-- Russia’s Milner Sets Up $3 Million Physics Prize, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2012-08-01T04:27:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-01/russia-s-milner-sets-up-3-million-physics-prize-vedomosti-says.html
Russian billionaire Yuri Milner
founded an annual prize for advances in physics and allied
fields with awards exceeding those of the  Nobel Prize ,  Vedomosti 
said, citing a statement from Milner’s charity fund.  The Fundamental Physics Prize Foundation, the board of
which includes Milner himself and Nobel Prize-winning physicist
Steven Weinberg, will award a prize worth $3 million and give
three others worth $100,000 each to young scientists, the
newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
